OL,3,CIsrael begins 'new wave' of strikes on
OL,4,CTehran, as US sinks Iranian warship
OL,6,FThe far-reaching conflict is causing
OL,7,Fsevere disruption in the global flow
OL,8,Fof crude oil, as the Strait of Hormuz,
OL,9,Fa major shipping route through which a
OL,10,Ffifth of global oil and gas supplies
OL,11,Fpass, was caught in the middle of the
OL,12,Fconflict.
OL,14,FIran controls the entire northern side
OL,15,Fof the Strait, effectively allowing it
OL,16,Fto wield the Strait as a geopolitical
OL,17,Fchokepoint.
OL,19,FWhile the strait is officially open,
OL,20,Ftrade has dropped by 80 per cent since
OL,21,FSaturday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/24
